description:
Welcome to a charming family lifestyle in this spacious modern home, thoughtfully designed for harmonious living and positioned in a wonderful community. Offering a light-filled open plan living with 4 spacious bedrooms and 2 living areas for gathering, retreating and entertaining. This home will cater to all with its versatility! Situated on a 504m2 block, the backyard wraps around the house creating space for entertaining, kids, pets and even the opportunity for a shed. Take advantage of being located on a corner block and side access for an additional storage options.

Kitchen: 20mm stone bench, island bench with breakfast bench, 900mm appliances, double sink, chrome fittings, built in pantry, overhead cabinetry, down lights, timber laminate, microwave provision

Living: Open plan adjoining kitchen/ living/ dining, down-lights, ducted heating, roller blinds, laminate floorboards, split system cooling, glass sliding doors through to the backyard, large windows to allow natural light flow through.

Second Living: Carpet, highlight windows with roller blinds, down lights, ducted heating,

Master bedroom: Carpet, windows with roller blinds, walk in robe, ducted heating.
Ensuite: 20mm stone bench, chrome fittings with handheld shower head, tile splash back, single vanity, open toilet

Additional bedrooms: Carpet, windows with roller blinds, built in robe, ducted heating

Main bathroom: 20mm stone bench, chrome fittings, single vanity, tile splash back, free standing bath, separate toilet

Outdoor: low maintenance, grass, garden beds, side access, corner block, well maintained front yard.

Mod cons: Front security door with electronic security pad, laundry with trough & outdoor access, laminate floor boards, ducted heating, split system heating & cooling, NBN/Opticomm access, remote controlled double car garage with rear and internal access. downlight to main living areas, side access, corner block

Ideal for: Families, investors, downsizers, first home buyers

Close by local facilities: Armstrong Creek Primary School, St Catherine of Siena Primary School, Elements Child Care Centre, Warralily Shopping Village, Armstrong Creek walking tracks, Horseshoe Bend access, Torquay Highway, Marshall Train Station and Waurn Ponds Shopping Centre

In line with government direction, all open home attendees must check in and show proof of vaccination certificate. If you do not have proof of double vaccination, please contact our office to arrange a private inspection
